# Contributing to PublicDev

First off, thank you for considering contributing to PublicDev! I appreciate your interest in making this extension even better.

## How to Contribute

There are many ways to contribute, including:

- **Reporting Bugs:** If you find a bug, please open an issue on [GitHub](https://github.com/harveenatwal/vscode-publicdev/issues) with a clear description, steps to reproduce, and expected behavior.
- **Suggesting Enhancements:** Have an idea for a new feature or improvement? Open an issue on [GitHub](https://github.com/harveenatwal/vscode-publicdev/issues) to share your thoughts.
- **Improving Documentation:** Found a typo or unclear explanation? You can submit a pull request to update the documentation.
- **Submitting Code Changes:** If you're a developer, you can contribute directly to the codebase. Please follow the guidelines below for submitting pull requests.

## Submitting Pull Requests

1. **Fork the repository:** Click the "Fork" button on the [GitHub](https://github.com/harveenatwal/vscode-publicdev) page to create your copy of the project.
2. **Create a branch:** Switch to a new branch for your changes (e.g., `git checkout -b feature/my-new-feature`).
3. **Make your changes:** Implement your feature or fix and write clear commit messages.
4. **Push your changes:** Push your branch to your fork (e.g., `git push origin feature/my-new-feature`).
5. **Open a pull request:** Go to the original repository and click the "New Pull Request" button. Follow the template and provide a detailed description of your changes.

## Development Setup

1. **Clone the repository:** `git clone https://github.com/harveenatwal/vscode-publicdev.git`
2. **Install dependencies:** `pnpm install`
3. **Run the extension:** Open VS Code, press `F5` to start a new Extension Development Host instance, and test your changes.

## Coding Style

- Follow the existing coding conventions in the project.
- Use clear variable and function names.
- Write concise and well-documented code.

## Additional Notes

- This project uses [semantic versioning](https://semver.org/) for releases.
- Please be patient while I review your pull request. I appreciate your contribution!
